column2:
converting annual interbank rates into monthly rates converting annual interbank rates into monthly rates to convert annual interbank interest rates into monthly rates, you need to account for the fact that there are 12 months in a year. the most common method is to use the formula for monthly rate = (1 + annual rate)^(1/12) - 1. this approach assumes that interest is compounded monthly. 

for example, if the annual interbank rate is 6%, or 0.06 in decimal form, the monthly rate can be calculated as follows: 

monthly rate = (1 + 0.06)^(1/12) - 1 ≈ 0.004867 or approximately 0 converting annual interbank rates into monthly rates,
